69.3	Chris_Gardner	Chris Gardner	Christopher Paul Gardner (born February 9, 1954 in Milwaukee, Wisconsin) is an American entrepreneur, investor, stock broker, motivational speaker, author, and philanthropist who, during the early 1980s, struggled with homelessness while raising his toddler son, Christopher, Jr. Gardner's book of memoirs, The Pursuit of Happyness, was published in May 2006.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/ChrisGardnerSept2011.jpg/220px-ChrisGardnerSept2011.jpg
